            <note xml:id="foot.f3">In <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6014.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Origin</hi></ref>, CD included a long section on embryology, arguing that since ‘the embryo is the animal in its less modified state’, it therefore ‘reveals the structure of its progenitor … Thus, community in embryonic structure reveals community of descent.’ (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6014.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Origin</hi></ref>, p. 449).</note>
